---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Use — Free Scrabble Word Finder" description="Terms of use for ScrabbleWordsFinder.com. Free to use, no sign-up required, provided as-is. Read our full terms for the instant Scrabble solver." keywords="terms of use, free scrabble word finder terms, no signup, instant solver terms">
  <nav class="mx-auto flex max-w-6xl items-center justify-between px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-800">
    <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xl font-bold tracking-tight">
      <span class="text-blue-400">Scrabble</span><span class="text-gray-300">WordsFinder</span>
    </a>
    <div class="flex items-center gap-6 text-sm text-gray-400">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Solver</a>
      <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Blog</a>
      <a href="/settings" class="hover:text-purple-400 transition-colors">⚙️</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-8">Last updated: January 2025</p>

    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6">By using ScrabbleWordsFinder.com ("the Service"), you agree to the following terms. If you don't agree, please don't use the Service.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-3">Free to Use</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">ScrabbleWordsFinder.com is provided free of charge. You may use the word solver, filters, saved words, and all other features without payment or registration. We reserve the right to introduce optional paid features in the future, but the core solver will always remain free.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-3">Service Provided "As Is"</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">The Service is provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis without warranties of any kind, whether express or implied, including but not limited to:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Accuracy or completeness of word lists</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Uninterrupted or error-free operation</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Fitness for any particular purpose</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Compatibility with official tournament word lists</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-3">Modifications to the Service</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">We may update, modify, or discontinue any part of the Service at any time without prior notice. This includes:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Adding or removing features</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Updating word dictionaries</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Changing the interface or functionality</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Performing maintenance or updates</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-3">User Responsibility</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">You are solely responsible for how you use the word results provided by this tool. This includes:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Compliance with tournament rules regarding electronic aids</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Verifying word validity for your specific dictionary version</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Using the tool ethically and in the spirit of fair play</span></li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-3">⚠️ See also: <a href="/disclaimer" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 underline underline-offset-2">Full Disclaimer</a> regarding tournament use and word validity.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-3">Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">ScrabbleWordsFinder.com and its operators shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages arising from:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Use or inability to use the Service</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Reliance on word results in competitive play</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Loss of saved data (stored in browser localStorage)</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Service interruptions or discontinuation</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-3">Intellectual Property</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">The design, code, and user interface of ScrabbleWordsFinder.com are the property of the xConvert24 team. Dictionary data is sourced from publicly available word lists (SOWPODS, TWL) and is not claimed as proprietary content.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-3">Changes to These Terms</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Changes will be reflected on this page with an updated "Last updated" date. Continued use of the Service after changes constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-3">Governing Terms</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">These terms constitute the entire agreement between you and ScrabbleWordsFinder.com regarding your use of the Service. If any provision is found to be unenforceable, the remaining provisions will continue in full force and effect.</p>

    <div class="border border-purple-800/50 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8 bg-gray-900/50">
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Questions about these terms? Contact us at <span class="text-blue-400">support@scrabblewordsfinder.com</span></p>
    </div>
  </div>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can I use ScrabbleWordsFinder for commercial purposes?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "ScrabbleWordsFinder is provided for personal, non-commercial use. Using our tool to build competing services or for automated scraping is prohibited." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are my responsibilities as a user?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Users agree to use the site lawfully, not attempt to disrupt the service, not submit harmful content through forms, and not use the tool during official tournament play." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can the terms of use change?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, we may update these terms from time to time. Continued use of the site after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated terms. The effective date is noted at the top." } }
  ]
}
</script>
</Layout>
